<chapter xml:id="db_pil_wui_applicationActivitiesView" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
    version="5.1" xml:lang="en-US">
    <title>Working With Application Activities</title>
    <para>Manage and track you application activities in the <guilabel>Application Activities</guilabel> view.</para>
    <para>The following actions are supported in the <guilabel>Application Activities</guilabel> view:</para>
    <itemizedlist>

        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="display_applicationActivities"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="display_applicationActivitiesDetails"/></para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
            <para><xref linkend="filter_applicationActivities"/></para>
        </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_applicationActivities">
        <title>Listing Application Activities</title>
        <para>You can display an overview of the configured application activities in the workspace of the <guilabel>Application Activities</guilabel> view.</para>
        <mediaobject><alt>Screenshot Application activities</alt><imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_ApplicationActivitiesView.png" width="14cm"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>The overview table displays the following information for each configured application by default:</para>
        <variablelist>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>ID</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The unique identifier (the sequence number) of the application activity.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Application</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>The application to which the activity is assigned.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Type</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Type of the application activity. The following values are currently supported:</para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><code>APPLICATION</code></para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para><code>MAIN</code></para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>State</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Application activity status. Valid values are:</para>
                    <itemizedlist>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>STARTED</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>FINISHED</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>FAILED</para>
                        </listitem>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>INTERRUPTED</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </itemizedlist>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
            <varlistentry>
                <term><guilabel>Created</guilabel></term>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Creation date and time of the application activity.</para>
                </listitem>
            </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="display_applicationActivitiesDetails">
        <title>Displaying Application Activity Details</title>
        <para>You can display the information about a specific application activity in the details pane. Currently, the details pane contains the same scope of information as the overview table.</para>
        <mediaobject><alt>Application Activities view with details</alt><imageobject>
                <imagedata fileref="images/scr_ApplicationActivitiesViewDetails.png" align="left" width="15cm"
                    format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
        </mediaobject>
        <para>Select the imported application activity from the overview table to display the application activity details.</para>

    </sect1>
    <sect1 xml:id="filter_applicationActivities">
        <title>Filtering Application Activities</title>
        <para>You can filter the existing application activities by ID (simple filter) or by other parameters (for more information about filter criteria, see <xref
                linkend="db_pil_wui_filterSettings"/>). A detailed description of the simple filter functionality can be found in <xref linkend="basic_filter"/>. A detailed description of the steps for advanced filter configurations can be found in <xref
                linkend="advanced_filter"/>.</para>
    </sect1>    
</chapter>